{"title":"Paul Comp’s New Tall & Elegant Zero Setback Seatpost Stands Next to Tall & Handsome","link":"https://bikerumor.com/paul-comps-new-tall-elegant-zero-setback-seatpost-stands-next-to-tall-handsome/","date":1772812800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"427\" alt=\"(Photos / Paul Components)\" /></p>\n<p>Bitchen news from Chico, California, as Paul Components releases a new seatpost. Hold on, don’t fret, Paul’s world-famous Tall &amp; Handsome seatpost isn’t going anywhere. But, if you’re looking for a seatpost with less setback than the Tall &amp; Handsome, then Paul’s new Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost might be your <a href=\"https://youtu.be/plD1MbOGLfQ?si=qUN6ymx5Dw0hI8ke\" target=\"_blank\">huckleberry</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-first-pic.jpeg\"><img width=\"600\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-first-pic.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-first-pic.jpeg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-first-pic-297x248.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-first-pic-120x100.jpeg 120w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / Paul Components)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s the deal… The Brooks B17 saddle has been in production and remains virtually unchanged since the 1880s. So, it’s not really a surprise that it doesn’t always play well with modern seatposts. Well, Paul Price (the “Paul” in Paul components) loves the Brooks B17. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, a while ago, he decided to make a seat post that would have enough setback to accommodate the B17’s painfully short seat rails. Thus, the birth of Paul’s <a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/shop/components/seatposts/tall-and-handsome/\" target=\"_blank\">Tall &amp; Handsome</a> seatpost</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-black-side-P.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-black-side-P.jpeg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-black-side-P.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-black-side-P-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-black-side-P-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-black-side-P-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Black</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-side-P.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-side-P.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost side P\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-side-P.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-side-P-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-side-P-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-side-P-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Silver</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Original Tall &amp; Handsome has a whopping 26mm of setback and is the perfect post to run a B17 without issue. I personally love the Brooks B17, and have owned many Tall &amp; Handsome posts over the years.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost came to fruition after listening to their customers’ requests. Customers wanted the same post, with the same design and attention to detail as the Tall &amp; Handsome, but <em>without</em> the 26mm setback. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-nad-window.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-nad-window.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost nad window\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-nad-window.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-nad-window-297x238.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-nad-window-120x96.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-nad-window-768x614.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tall &amp; Elegant maintains the brand’s famous focus on practical adjustability and durability while offering a straight mounting position. The design centers around user-friendly adjustability. The two adjustment bolts are spaced far enough apart to make it easy to use standard multi-tools for trailside adjustments or torque wrenches in the shop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-in-use-e1772650657326.jpeg\"><img width=\"1024\" height=\"1110\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-in-use-e1772650657326.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-in-use-e1772650657326.jpeg 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-in-use-e1772650657326-277x300.jpeg 277w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-in-use-e1772650657326-111x120.jpeg 111w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-in-use-e1772650657326-768x833.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p> The dual-bolt system prevents saddle rail slippage, while spherical stainless steel washers allow the bolt heads to pivot and self-align to the saddle cradle. The top clamp incorporates two brass trunnions that reduce friction and prevent binding during angle changes. This makes for nice, smooth tilt adjustments.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fore and aft saddle adjustment is easily done by loosening both screws equally. There is also approximately 15-degrees of tilt adjustment range as well. And if you need to micro-adjust, the rider simply loosens one bolt while tightening the other. The new Tall &amp; Elegant also accomodates carbon railed saddles. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-purple-side-P.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-purple-side-P.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost purple side P\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-purple-side-P.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-purple-side-P-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-purple-side-P-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-purple-side-P-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Purple</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-polished-side-P.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-polished-side-P.jpeg\" alt=\"Paul Comp Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost polished side P\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-polished-side-P.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-polished-side-P-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-polished-side-P-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Paul-Comp-Tall-Elegant-Seatpost-polished-side-P-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Polished</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tall &amp; Elegant Retail &amp; Detail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $286</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Material: 2024/6061 Aluminum</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Weight: 327-402g</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Finish: Black, Purple, Polished, or Silver</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Diameters: 27.2, 30.9, 31.6</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Machined by us in sunny Chico, California</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The fabulous, new Tall &amp; Elegant Seatpost is currently available through Paul Components’ link below or at most local bike shops. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">PaulComp.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/paul-comps-new-tall-elegant-zero-setback-seatpost-stands-next-to-tall-handsome/\">Paul Comp’s New Tall &amp; Elegant Zero Setback Seatpost Stands Next to Tall &amp; Handsome</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3abd6d0650fee14158b4f7d3310f2be12daff1632f1c213058a716bbd4e94a67","category":"Cycling"}